  "texts": [
    "Variational Autoencoders (VAEs) and GANs can be trained to learn latent representations of sensory input, enabling the generation of new molecular or sensory profiles that mimic real taste patterns.",
    "This approach supports virtual screening of novel flavor compounds and assists in the design of synthetic formulations with targeted taste attributes.",
    "While still in early development, these models show promise in accelerating flavor innovation by reducing reliance on time-consuming and resource-intensive sensory experiments.",
    "Reinforcement learning (RL) is also gaining attention in gustatory modeling, particularly for its potential in ingredient informatics and recipe optimization.",
    "Unlike supervised or generative approaches that rely on fixed datasets, RL agents learn to make sequential decisions by interacting with an environment."
  ],
